snippet.title: Bertrum Jean gives emotional testimony about his son Botham Jean
snippet.description:
The jurors who convicted Amber Guyger of murdering Botham Jean heard more testimony Wednesday during the sentencing phase of the fired officer's trial.

Guyger, 31, spent the night in the Dallas County Jail after the jury found her guilty Tuesday for shooting and killing 26-year-old Jean in his home last year. Guyger was off-duty but still in her Dallas police uniform when she shot Jean. She testified that she mistook Jean's apartment for hers and thought he was a burglar.
